# Chrome extension signing private key — NEVER commit it.
# Load-unpacked debugging uses the public "key" in manifest.json (which fixes
# the extension id); the .pem is only needed to package a .crx for distribution,
# and should be kept out of git (e.g. in a password manager) and copied between
# machines through a secure channel — not the repo.
*.pem
.extension-key.pem

# Packaging output of `npm run package`; regenerated, never committed.
chrome-extension.zip
